reviews.review_text: Their lamb souvlaki was great!!! So delicious! Good service and sever is so friendly. They have a lot of types of beer on the tap and cans. You can find your favorite flavor. And they have a nice patio, I love it! Id like to go there again for sure.

This is now the second experience I have at this location I did the abba experience it also took me 30 minutes to get my food but when the show is completely sold out and it look like 100 plus people I can see why and I liked the food, Entertainment and staff The singers did do a great job at making sure everyone was included in the experience Today I did the broadway experience and once again it was a packed house. Again it took some time to get my meal but I have been to many restaurants and when busy this is the case so I was prepared. My burger was yummy and crispy fries The 3 singers did such amazing job big energy and once again the experience was amazing Told the show manager Kim how impressed I was and looking forward to more of these shows

Zawa is a great spot for a casual bite to eat and a drink. Loads of food options, the Zaatar and Lahma Bajeen are so tasty and great for sharing. The servers are really friendly and they also have Murphy s on draught which is a big plus!

We had a great evening!  The food was good and our server Emily was wonderful and made our night   she even played Pink Martini for us when we were rained out of their concert!  We ll definitely be back!

I come here all the time because: 1. The Chef s salad is damn good, it keeps me coming back. It s simple and it s solid and I feel good after I eat it! 2. It s lowkey here, it s quiet, I always get my favourite table, and I can hang out and be in peace! Good service, and a damn great salad.

Awesome place to go on a hot sunny day to sit and people watch on the patio... Great staff, awesome food & one of my favorites is the Greek salad yum!! * Update ..this is a trio platter?  And poutine yum!!!

Have been twice so far and am pleaslenty surprised on how good the food is. Seems this place  had a firesale with the previous employees cause their is only 1 server but shes a real sweetheart, had a great st Pattys day there even if it was brief. (Recommend this place) only issue I would have is the owner peaking and sneaking around corners to see how you were enjoying the stay.

Zawa is a great spot for casual eats and drinks. The restaurant is big and cozy ,good vibe and great service. Food came out quickly , I had a burger with fries which were really great . They have a good selection of beer on tap. Overall it s a fun place to check out with friends.

This place should be supported for many different reasons. Food option are varied and they have introduced vegan chikun nuggets and chikun burger for those who want to enjoy the taste without the cruelty. Prices are fair considering the times and city we live in. This place has supported us many time and its our turn to support them! UPDATE After Many years coming here I can say it is one of the few original places left in the area. I love it and I think people should support it considering that it is a family owned business who puts their heart in it. Update! I love how this place is everything but pretentious and always welcomes you as a family. These businesses should be supported! P.S. also the staff leaving was just 2 people not the team. People stayed because they know what is true and what isnt!

reviews.review_text: Stumbled in after a punk show and the kitchen was closed but they fed us anyway and it was delishhhhh. The server was very sweet even though it was late!
Great people, amazing ambiance on the Drive! Always down for a beer if Zawa is the place.

I went to Zawa for the first time for breakfast. I had amazing service and great food and reasonable prices. The establishment was very welcoming and made me feel like home. I would definitely recommend!
Nice place) with some special atmospheres. With good tasty kitchen.
Old skoo. Great staff. Great location. Look, I never ate a thing but judging by the place you already know its good.

Finally tried Zawa last night with my girlfriend. Lovely relaxed atmosphere. Was so worth it, I did not get the servers name but she wore a white dress with a smile and provide amazing service, Was alone but was fast in doing her rounds to the customers both inside and on the patio. She also made the drinks which as promised were delicious and strong! Also shout out to the chef for the Delicious pasta dishes we had, Tasted like homemade. Will definitely comeback.

The best food on the drive, very affordable drinks  the best in town. Great service, every time I come to Vancouver, I go there! Honestly why wait in line for an hour for biercraft, Havanas or fets. Walk a little further and find a table right away. Enjoy a good selection of draft and cheesy delicious food at reasonable prices. With kind staff that arent exhausted and are actually happy you came. Do it, you wont be upset.
Food is delicious, the beer is great and the owner of the restaurant is one of the nicest people I have met. 10/10 recommend.
Loved it ate with my family and felt welcome
Great service, beer selection and l had the best poutine! I love their quite environment and clean washrooms. New fav spot!

This place has amazing food. The one thing I like though is there Clubhouse sandwich. It is one of the best clubhouse sandwiches I have ever had in the entire city of Vancouver. The owner is a good man. Really nice. Really good to his customers. The staff are awesome.
Absolutely love it here, nice chill atmosphere, relaxed vibe and good customer service, the drink specials are great too.

3 of us had dinner.  Salads, soups, mussels and frits.  All the dishes were excellent, well presented and the service was as good as the food.  Wine was also very good.  And the prices were very affordable.  Asked the waitress why the reviews on the internet were so poor.  She was an excellent waitress and had been there only a month.  She said the cook was also fairly new.
Great food & friendly staff! Menu is diverse and they even have a nice bar

I love their patio.  It has great shade on hot days or sunny spots if you need to catch the rays. Zawa has a great selection of beers and appys.  I usually have one of their salads topped with chicken and my husband has a burger.  It is affordably priced unlike some other spots on the drive. I have also known the owner for years and he is a warm and generous man.

When up by Commercial drive and looking for a good meal recommend checking out Zawa, we did for breakfast and will definitely be back to check out their dinner menu. Regular breaky items plus some specialty such as cajun sausage omelet (if you like spicy hot that is), both were great. Service was friendly and efficient completing the meal experience.

On July 8th 2018, during my visit of the Car Free Day on Commercial Drive, I was looking for a place that served vegy burgers. I was about to walk pass this restaurant because I saw very few customers on the patio and hardly any inside. I asked for the menu, sat down, and saw they had just what I wanted. So I ordered one with yam fries. When it arrived at my table on the patio, thier vegy burger was much better than I thought! A large burger with interesting looking yam fries. Delicious! I regret not having taken a photo of it.
Surprisingly awesome breakfast delicious had the country breakfast

When I rate something theres seldom middle ground. I love it or hate it & I only hate something if it does not live up to its claims.  My time is not wasted on anything that IN MY EYES would not be, for me, a 5 star experience. I am not saying these are Michelin Stars -they are MY STARS and as such, are mostly subjective. To qualify my opinions, I am extraordinarily well travelled and have enjoyed the finest hospitality that can be offered. Zawa was for me a 5 star experience proportional to what the establishment could reasonably be considered capable of offering. I was meeting a friend for coffee & suggested Zawa, as Ive  been walking past for about a year, enticed each time by the desert menu posted out front. My companion decided on a meal a meal and ordered their Vegan burger. He was well pleased and it looked & smelled deeelish!! AS FOR MY CAKE -I am happy to report that the heavy, rich pure dark chocolate slice with  GENEROUS HELPINGS of vanilla ice cream AND whipped cream, equalled any (similar) chocolate cake I have had in what are among the worlds finest French & Belgian restaurants. ...to expand that statement ...SIMILAR is the operative word ... I would not suppose Zawa to serve tableside flambe & create warm, liqueur-based sauces to go with a piece of gateau. OUR SERVER WAS DELIGHTFUL!! Friendly, knowledgable about the menu & accommodating.  Ive noticed theres always a nice clientele & usually a few customers during off-peak times. We were there from about 3pm to 4:15 -before dinner hours & to my great pleasure, were the ONLY customers. THIS IS IMPORTANT because I am a musician and as such, am greatly affected by noise, chatter, background music and the like. They are almost impossible for me to ignore & make enjoyment a struggle. When business slows, my experience has been that staff entertain themselves while catching up on the more menial tasks by pumping the volume of their favourite tunes -or WORSE turning on a TV. At Zawa the music REMAINED in the background -as did our waitress -attentive when we wanted something but didnt hover or make endless returns to our table citing by rote the familiar, Can I get you guys anything else?   We chatted for over an hour and NOT ONCE were we pressured into ordering more, NOR was the bill put on the table ...an unspoken implication the server has decided its time for you to settle up and move on. Therefore ...for me, ZAWA was a 5 star experience & I will go again and bring other people. xoxo :)

Server was slammed. Handled it well. Slight wait for the drinks but that was to be expected. Owner, I forget his name, walking around . He was pretty nice once I spoke with him. Nice attention to detail.
Great place on The Drive. Great food and atmosphere. Sal has a great staff and always a friendly jive! 20 + years!! Its an after Britannia hockey thing!!

I decided to walk down the drive and found this GEM.. prices are cheap and the food it AWESOME.. I had their burger and had a hard time finishing it.. They also have Heineken on draft... will definitely return... why because the staff are older and they give exceptional service...
I have been here a couple times and the veggie burger is really amazing! Must have.
Good variety on the menu. Prompt service by gracious waitresses. Great atmosphere. Great community restaurant for watching sports. I go all the time. Great place.
I really love this place.  The breakfasts are awesome, especially their crabcake Benny.  Every time I go I try the soups. They are all homemade and always bang on.  It s a hidden gem.
Im regular customer, Zawa is very friendly and welcoming place, plus they have the best salmon and roast lamb in the town. Thank you Zawa staff and please keep up the good work.. Cheers
We live in the neighbourhood and go here often for cheap beer and food. Its never busy and the food is very good. The waitresses are always nice and the service is good.
I would call this a premium dive. Its got so much space for big parties and has decent food. Went for brunch, had a caesar, waitress was super nice.  Loved it ~

Great food and servers. Menu has great selection from burgers, Greek or pasta. I personally liked the calamari, fish and chips or pasta
